                <fr:title text="The zero matrix">The zero matrix</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>zero <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS.xml" title="Matrix over a semiring" addr="jms-00IS" type="local">matrix</fr:link></html:strong></html:em> is one that whose cells all contain <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex>. In particular, we have:</html:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
   \mathbf {0} &\in  \mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\\
   \mathbf {0}_{i,j} &= 0
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
