        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>21</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-00JV/0</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JV/0.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The adjacency matrix of the reflexive-transitive closure › "><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JV.xml" title="The adjacency matrix of the reflexive-transitive closure" addr="jms-00JV" type="local">The <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JN.xml" title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph" addr="jms-00JN" type="local">adjacency matrix</fr:link> of the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JH.xml" title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation" addr="jms-00JH" type="local">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We first unravel the first few <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex>’s</html:span> to get a better understanding.</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   M_1 &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  M_0\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n\oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  I^n\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n \oplus  M
   \\
   M_2 &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  M_1\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  {\mathopen {}\left (I^n \oplus  M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  I^n\right )\mathclose {}} \oplus  {\mathopen {}\left (M\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}
   \\
   &= I^n \oplus  M \oplus  M^2
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>By induction, we can extend the pattern above to a closed form for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex>. In particular, we deduce that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k = \bigoplus _{l\leq  k} M^l]]></fr:tex> by recalling from <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J3.xml" title="Associativity and unit laws of matrix products" addr="jms-00J3" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00J3" /></fr:link> that the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IT.xml" title="The identity matrix" addr="jms-00IT" type="local">identity matrix</fr:link> is the neutral element for <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV.xml" title="Product of matrices" addr="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix multiplication</fr:link>. Therefore, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n =\bigoplus _{k \leq  n}M^k]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Our goal is to show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}} R^{\circ  *}]]></fr:tex>; we have already seen in <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JR.xml" title="Matrix addition and union of relations" addr="jms-00JR" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00JR" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J2.xml" title="Matrix product is relational composition" addr="jms-00J2" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00J2" /></fr:link> that <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JO.xml" title="Pointwise addition of matrices" addr="jms-00JO" type="local">matrix addition</fr:link> corresponds to union of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link> and <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV.xml" title="Product of matrices" addr="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix multiplication</fr:link> corresponds to <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composition</fr:link>.</html:p>

 <html:p>By <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JU.xml" title="Reflexive-transitive closure of finite endo-relations" addr="jms-00JU" type="local">Observation <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00JU" /></fr:link> (<fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JU.xml" title="Reflexive-transitive closure of finite endo-relations" addr="jms-00JU" type="local">reflexive-transitive closure of <html:em>finite</html:em> <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JF.xml" title="Path in a directed graph" addr="jms-00JF" type="local">endo-relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}]]></fr:tex>. Therefore:</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ *} = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>By <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JR.xml" title="Matrix addition and union of relations" addr="jms-00JR" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00JR" /></fr:link> (<fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JR.xml" title="Matrix addition and union of relations" addr="jms-00JR" type="local"><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JO.xml" title="Pointwise addition of matrices" addr="jms-00JO" type="local">matrix addition</fr:link> and union of <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}
  =
  \bigoplus _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 By <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J2.xml" title="Matrix product is relational composition" addr="jms-00J2" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00J2" /></fr:link> (<fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J2.xml" title="Matrix product is relational composition" addr="jms-00J2" type="local"><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV.xml" title="Product of matrices" addr="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix product</fr:link> is <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composition</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \bigoplus _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}  =
  \bigoplus _{k\leq  n} {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\right )\mathclose {}}^k
  =
  \bigoplus _{k\leq  n} M^k
  = M_n
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter>
