            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>For natural numbers <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, an <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-matrix</html:span></html:strong></html:em> over a semiring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (S,0,\oplus ,1,\odot \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is given by entries <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M_{i,j}\in  S]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We will write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for the set of <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-matrices</html:span></html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
